										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I think it&#8217;s safe to say that the workhorse of industry in the 1870s was coal.  They used it for all those lovely steam engines, to warm their homes, and of course for the occasional charcoal drawings.  But did you know that 60 years before Henry Ford was even born, a guy named <a title="Ansad Petrol history page" href="http://ansadpetrol.com/history4.html" target="_blank">Gasimbey Mansurbeyov</a> was drilling for oil, offshore in the Caspian Sea?  They weren&#8217;t using oil for gasoline, but Baku, the city at the heart of the oil business in Azerbaijan, was already getting rich off the profits of oil.  Go figure.</p>
<p>Here&#8217;s some nice photos of Baku.  It&#8217;s a neat looking city.<span id="more-191"></span></p>
<div style="width: 311px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="http://azer.com/aiweb/categories/magazine/ai102_folder/102_articles/102_oil_chronology.html" target="_blank"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" class="  " alt="" src="http://azer.com/aiweb/categories/magazine/ai102_folder/102_photos/102_370_oil_fields.jpg" width="301" height="181" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Oil fields near Baku</p></div>
<div style="width: 298px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_City_(Baku)" target="_blank"><img decoding="async" class="   " alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/59/Sheikh_ibrahim_mosque_-Old_City_Baku_Azerbaijan_built_in_1415.jpg/800px-Sheikh_ibrahim_mosque_-Old_City_Baku_Azerbaijan_built_in_1415.jpg" width="288" height="206" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">A bit of 15th century Baku.</p></div>
<div style="width: 305px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="http://www.brodyaga.com/pages/viewlarge.php?id=4541&amp;cty=Baku&amp;place=Azerbaijan,%20Azerbaijan" target="_blank"><img decoding="async" class="     " alt="" src="http://www.brodyaga.com/pages/photos/Azerbaijan/Azerbaijan%20Azerbaijan%201158456569.jpg" width="295" height="222" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Baku&#8217;s House of Government.</p></div>
<div style="width: 370px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="http://www.so-many-places.com/2013/01/a-quick-guide-to-baku-azerbaijan/" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="  " alt="" src="http://www.so-many-places.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/baku-01.jpg" width="360" height="193" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Baku today. So pretty&#8230;.</p></div>
